message.content:
1. There were treatment groups being compared in a study.
2. The study looked at rates of exclusive breastfeeding.
3. The study also looked at rates of any breastfeeding.
4. The study measured these rates at discharge, 3 months, and 6 months of infants' age.
5. There was no evidence of difference between treatment groups in the rates of exclusive breastfeeding at discharge.
6. The p-value for the rates of exclusive breastfeeding at discharge was 0.2.
7. There was no evidence of difference between treatment groups in the rates of any breastfeeding at discharge.
8. The p-value for the rates of any breastfeeding at discharge was >0.99.
9. There was no evidence of difference between treatment groups in the rates of exclusive breastfeeding at 3 months.
10. The p-value for the rates of exclusive breastfeeding at 3 months was 0.12.
11. There was no evidence of difference between treatment groups in the rates of any breastfeeding at 3 months.
12. The p-value for the rates of any breastfeeding at 3 months was 0.10.
13. There was no evidence of difference between treatment groups in the rates of exclusive breastfeeding at 6 months.
14. The p-value for the rates of exclusive breastfeeding at 6 months was 0.45.
15. There was no evidence of difference between treatment groups in the rates of any breastfeeding at 6 months.
16. The p-value for the rates of any breastfeeding at 6 months was 0.34.

messages.content:
Statement: We found no evidence of difference between treatment groups in the rates of exclusive as well as any breastfeeding at discharge (p-value 0.2 and >0.99 respectively), 3 months (p-value 0.12 and 0.10) and 6 months of infants’ age (p-value 0.45 and 0.34 respectively).
